summary: Honestly, as excited as i am about the new captain marvel movie coming out soon, the casting bugs me. Like it feels like a...
body: Honestly, as excited as i am about the new captain marvel movie coming out soon, the casting bugs me. Like it feels like a missed opportunity to cast pink as captain marvel, only because thats who I always thought a real life Carol Danvers would look like. No hate on the actress playing her in the coming movie, just thoughts that i have.

tags: ant man and the was spoilers
summary: Spoiler for “Ant-man and the wasp”/Captain Marvel theory!
body:
Spoiler for “Ant-man and the wasp”/Captain Marvel theory!

Pym mentioned that Scott can get sucked into “time vortexes” while in the macrospace. Captain Marvel is set in the 90’s and we never saw her up until now where she somehow didn’t age since the 90’s.

My theory is that the post credit scene of captain marvel will be Scott pulling her into a time vortex and bringing her into the present. This would explain why she hasn’t been seen until now and why she’s a last resort for Fury. It’s because she’s been “missing” since the 90’s and Nick wasn’t even sure if she was alive. He hit that button out of desperation and the hope that she’s somehow out there still.

I can see the post credit scene ending with captain marvel back on earth with Scott and they both look up and see the destruction caused by Thanos. Scott then gets a call from his ex wife that Cassie had turned to dust along with the others around them. Scott drops his phone and realizes what the three piles of ash are on the ground now. As he breaks down and cries, he says “what could’ve done this?”

Then Carol takes a deep breath and says “Thanos.” Before the screen cuts to black.
